Prophet Muhammad (570-632 A.D)
 He is the founder of Islam. In 570-571 AD, in the Arabian city
of Mecca, Islamic Prophet of God Hazarat Muhammad was
born in a Quarish Family.
 At the age of 25, he married a 40 years Old Khadijah bint
Khuwaylid. She was the first Muslim to embrace (after
Muhammad) Islam.
 In 622 AD, Muhammad migrated to Medina and this event is
called Hijra, marking the beginning of Islamic Calendar.
 So, derived from Hijra, the calendar is called Hijri Calender.
 The number of followers increased and in 630 AD
Muhammad returned to Mecca and established his
eminence. When he died in 632 AD, Islam had started
propagating.
Arab Invasion in India
• Muhammad-bin-Qasim
 Al-Hajjajj, the Governor of Iraq sent his nephew
Muhammad-bin-Qasim to India
 He Conquered Sind with the permission of Caliph Walid
• Battle of Rewar fought between Muhammad-bin-Qasim
and Dahir (a Brahmin) the ruler of Sind
• Dahir was defeated. Sind and Multan was captured.
• Muhammad-bin-Qasim called Multan as ‘The City of Gold’.
• Arab conquest of Sindh resulted in spread of Islam to North
India.
• The wife of Dahir Rani Bai and the other women of Sind put up a
heroic defense within the Fort of Rewar.
Administrative System
• But Islam was first introduced by Malik
Ibn Dinar in Kerlala in 644 A.D.
• Sind and Multan were divided into number
of Iqtas or districts by Muhammad-binQasim and Arab military officers headed
the Iqtas.
• The sub-divisions of the districts were
administered by the local Hindu Officers.
• Jizya was imposed on non-Muslims.
