METALLOIDS
• They possess the characteristics of both metals as well as non metal.
• They are called metalloids and semi- metals have mostly non-metallic properties.
• One of their distinguishing characteristics is that their conductivity increases as
their temperature increases.
• While normal metal conductivity decreases with the increase in temperature. This
property is known as semi conductance and the materials are called semiconductors.
• They are important in digital electronics, such as computers.
• The metalloids include elements such as Boron , Silicon, Germanium, Arsenic,
Antimony and Tellurium.
