Organic Chemistry
By Dr Vipan Goyal

ORGANIC CHEMISTRY
• It studies the structure, properties and reactions of organic
compounds, which contain carbon in covalent bonding.
• Organic compounds is a carbon- containing chemical compound.
• Covalent bonds and tetra valency are the characteristics of carbons
having 4 as valency.
• Covalent bonds are formed by sharing of bonds between carbon
and other compounds.
ORGANIC CHEMISTRY
• Carbon shows catenation property (Catenation is the linkage of atoms of
the same element into longer chains.
• Catenation occurs most readily in carbon, which forms covalent bonds
with other carbon atoms to form longer chains and structures.)
• HYDROCARBONS
 A hydrocarbon is an organic compound consisting entirely of hydrogen
and carbon.
 Tetravalent compounds
 EX:-C5H12, pentane
ISOMERS
• The compound which has same chemical formula but have different
physical and chemical properties.
HYDROCARBONS
• SATURATED HYDROCARBONS
 Compounds formed by carbon - carbon single bond
