• Blood Leukemia : Abnormal increase
in WBCs i.e. Blood Cancer
• Neutrophils, eosinophil and
basophils are different types of
granulocytes/ has granules (small
particles) released during
infections, while lymphocytes and
monocytes are the agranulocytes.
Neutrophils
• Most abundant cells (60-65 per cent)
