Basophil
• It contains heparin, histamine, chemotactic factors and chronic
reactive material for allergic reaction.
• Functions:
 It is also involved in allergic reaction.
 Histamine increase permeability of capillary and contract bronchia
smooth muscle, and result in allergic reaction such as measles,
asthama.
• Basophils secrete histamine, serotonin, heparin, etc., and are
