He was son of Akbar’s trusted caretaker, Bairam Khan. After
Bairam’s Khan was murdered, Bairam Khan’s wife became the
second wife of Akbar. Translation of Babarnama into Persian;
accorded Khan-i-Khanan title by Akbar. Although a Muslim by
birth, he was a devotee of Lord Krishna.
