• The Mughal ministers did not constitute a Cabinet in the modern sense of term.
They were basically secretaries. The initiation of the policies was in the hands of
the emperor.
• The first finance minister of Akbar was Muzaffar Khan.
• Todar Mal, Muzaffar Khan and Shah Mansur were the three most notable finance
ministers of Akbar and all the three were skilled financiers and first-rate
administrators.
