Officers During the Vedic Period
Name Function
Kshatri Chamberlain
Sthapati Chief Judge
Mahishi Chief Queen
Govikartana Keeper of forests & games
Akshavapa Accountant
Takshan Carpenter
Economic structure
• Agriculture was the chief occupation.
• Industrial work like metal work, pottery and carpentry work also
was there.
• There was foreign trade also with Babylon.
• The plough was known as Sira and the furrow Sita.
• Many types of grains were grown, such as rice, barley, beans,
and sesame. Their seasons are also mentioned as barley sown in
winter, ripened in summer; rice sown in the rains, reaped in
autumn and son on.
Economic structure
• The Satapatha Brahmana mentions various operations of
agriculture such as ploughing, sowing, reaping, and threshing.
• Niska and Satamana were the units of currency.
• The term Bali was used for a voluntary gift to chief (initially),
but later on, it become a regular tax. It was collected to
maintain the political and administrative structure.
